<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-29T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A PW/5–2945.: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-29T20:00:00+01:00">May
                                        29, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received May 29—6:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2941. American Interests—Far East. Dept’s 1736, May 7. Gorgé replies
                                he already made several representations Japs in effort obtain
                                remedial action but these brought no result. Has strongly intervened
                                with Minister Togo basis reference telegram.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>